!!VRz10:S^You have defeated the Killer Rabbit of Caerbannog?  Right, then!
I will not hinder your quest - mad as it seems!  The Portals' power
comes from a turbine, which I, Tim, D.M.T. (Deus Machina Turbinorum)
designed!  Unfortunately, it is south of the Dead Zone.^;
!!VRz12:S^Tim the Enchanter^;
!!VRz13:S^..\Data\SND_Tim1.jpg^;
!!IF:D33/z10/0/z12/z13 ;
!!IF:F33/0/0/0/0/0;
!!IF:E99/33;
!!UN:S61/118/0/3/8; show compressor and buttons
!!UN:S76/104/0/3/9; show HPIP
!!VRz10:S^So ever since Megathon and his creatures took over the Southlands,
no one has been able to get to the machine for service and refueling.
I heard Lord Morrolan's expedition planned to dig a tunnel under the
Dead Zone.  Perhaps you could use that.^;
!!VRz12:S^Tim the Enchanter^;
!!VRz13:S^..\Data\SND_Tim1.jpg^;
!!IF:D33/z10/0/z12/z13 ;
!!IF:F33/0/0/0/0/0;
!!IF:E99/33;
!!VRz10:S^Fuel?  It will run on almost anything.  A few tons of coal, 10
barrels of oil - but the most powerful fuel is Electrum.  A single liter
of Electrum would be enough to start the turbine.  We had a smelter set
up, but it is probable no longer operational.  You might ask - no.^;
!!VRz12:S^Tim the Enchanter^;
!!VRz13:S^..\Data\SND_Tim1.jpg^;
!!IF:D33/z10/0/z12/z13 ;
!!IF:F33/0/0/0/0/0;
!!IF:E99/33;
!!UN:S60/104/0/3/5; show fuel tank
!!VRz10:S^I was going to say, the Storm Giants, but to reach them you would
have to traverse the Perilous Passes of the Stone Men!  And even then
the Storm Giants might not give you any.  They drink it for the energy
they need to generate lightning.^;
!!VRz12:S^Tim the Enchanter^;
!!VRz13:S^..\Data\SND_Tim1.jpg^;
!!IF:D33/z10/0/z12/z13 ;
!!IF:F33/0/0/0/0/0;
!!IF:E99/33;
!!UN:S96/115/0/3/6; show Passes
!!VRz10:S^Then there is the problem of the Generator.  Everytime we shut down
we had to clear the Generator of bugs before we could start up again.
Circuit problems?  No, bugs - giant bugs from another dimension.  How
they get in is a mystery, but the intense electrical field attracts them.^;
!!VRz12:S^Tim the Enchanter^;
!!VRz13:S^..\Data\SND_Tim1.jpg^;
!!IF:D33/z10/0/z12/z13 ;
!!IF:F33/0/0/0/0/0;
!!IF:E99/33;
!!UN:S99/82/0/3/5; show generator
!!VRz10:S^Good luck!  Here, take my ring.  It will help you, and when you
have enough experience under your belt, it will authorize the Guild to
make you an Enchanter, like me!  (You'll have to find your own
Enchanter's Hat, though.  Mine isn't for sale.)^;
!!VRz12:S^Tim the Enchanter^;
!!VRz13:S^..\Data\SND_Tim1.jpg^;
